commit.message:
Add uxntal-compile-and-run function

This does what it sounds like -- it runs uxnasm and then
runs uxnemu on the resulting ROM. It supports a list of
extra optional arguments (e.g. "-2x") as well as a
configurable path to uxnemu.

commit.message:
Update to modern uxntal syntax.

This does a few things:

 - removes literal characters (')
 - adds new raw addresses (_ - =)
 - adds instant jumps (! ? [])

It's not possible for the syntax highlighter to
distinguish macro calls from instant JSR, so
currently we assume the latter.
include MELPA badge and installation notes

Set up M-x compile in a more direct way.

Also use tabs instead of spaces when requested.

Rename tal-mode -> uxntal-mode in README.

Fixes #3

Respond to review comments and general improvements.

In particular:

 1. Renames the mode to uxntal-mode
 2. Derives the major mode from prog-mode
 3. Clean up some imprecision around truth checks
 4. Add defcustom for uxnasm location
 5. Improve indentation
 6. Fix bug with comment-region, etc.

commit.message:
Improve the ability to explain Uxntal words.

This commit unifies the previous support for explaining
Uxntal instructions and numeric constants to include most
other syntax as well. Rather than having to choose the
correct commmand to run for a given word, we reuse the
regular expressions used for syntax highlighting.

Additionally, the file has been restrucuted to be more
compliant with MELPA requirements.

Improve highlighting, add imenu support.

This commit does a few things:

 - introduces a tal-mode:strict-comments setting (default t)
 - improves strict comment highlighting to handle \n and \t
 - adds imenu support for macros and labels
